{"word":"ἐνοπή","slug":"ἐνοπή","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐνοπή</b></el> <el>(ἐνοπή, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐνέπω'><el>ἐνέπω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a crying, screaming</i>, as of birds, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>: <i>a war-cry</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>generally, <i>a voice</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>of things, <i>a sound</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}